Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: At the Corner of Danforth Ave & Morton Rd

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 2301-2315 Danforth Avenue retail comprises of 4,255 sq. ft. of prime retail space under a brand new 8 storey condominium building constructed by Marlin Springs. Located on the southwest corner of Danforth Avenue and Morton Road, this new development sits at the edge of the Danforth Village and adjacent to the Upper Beaches neighbourhood.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: At the Corner of Danforth Ave & Morton Rd

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Four units totalling 4,255 sq. ft. of prime retail space for sale under a brand new 8 storey condominium building with over 166 residential units. The Property provides users and investors with an opportunity to acquire transit connected right-sized space at the edge of the Danforth Village adjacent to the Upper Beaches neighbourhood.

The Property provides users and investors with an opportunity to acquire brand new, transit connected right-sized space. 1624-1630 Queen Street East comprises of 5,865 sq. ft. of prime retail space and two parking spaces under a brand new 6 storey condominium building constructed by Marlin Springs. Located in the Beach neighbourhood, one of Toronto’s most sought after neighbourhoods known for it’s smalltown feel and retail strip of local cafes, restaurants and independent retailers.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Conveniently located just west of the Annex in Seaton Villag
Conveniently located just west of the Annex in Seaton Villag

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 6,000 sq. ft. of land in an up and coming residential neighbourhood with upside in future rents. Three two-storey buildings with 3 retail units and 7 apartment units and basements. Vacant possession. Located in a desirable neighbourhood with easy access to schools, parks and public transportation. Many new developments in the area including Bianca by Tridel, Lithos by RioCan & ANX by Freed. Application submitted for a 14 unit apartment and 3 commercial unit reconfiguration. Potential to purchase 262 Christie on its own or acquire 258 and 260 Christie as a package separate from 262 Christie

Prime retail property at 786-796 Lawrence Avenue West and 8-12 Bagnato situated just east of the busy intersection of Dufferin and Lawrence. The property comprises of 26,604 sq. ft. of ground floor retail, which is currently anchored by the provincial government. The property has excellent visibility with great frontage on Lawrence Avenue West. The property is being offered with 17 parking spaces which are currently being used by Infrastructure Ontario. Additional spaces are available if desired. Offers will be reviewed on an As-Received Basis
